  "texts": [
    "Also called \"confabulation.\"",
    "Continued on next pageTABLE V -continued from previous page Num.",
    "Author(s) Year Application Definition Citation 308 Coskun et al. [327] 2023 Health/ ChatGPT \"AI hallucination\" refers to situations where the AI generates responses that are not derived from its training data, potentially leading to inaccuracies or misunderstandings.",
    "309 Lam [328] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" refers to occurrences where AI models output plausible but factually incorrect information.",
    "310 Pantanowitz and Pantanowitz [329] 2023 Health/ ChatGPT \"AI hallucination\" occurs when the AI imagines facts that are not real as being real or makes reasoning errors that it should not be making. 311 Boussen et al."
